<p>👋 I’m a frontend software engineer with a decade of experience. I'm currently a full-time contractor at Eventbrite, building out components for the Marmalade Design System, so that new designs in 2024 can be built without Eventbrite's legacy design system. As my contract is winding down, I am looking for full-time or contract work!</p>

<p>I am a product-minded developer with a focus on the frontend. Throughout my career, I’ve been drawn toward problem solving around User Experience (UX) and Developer Experience (DX). At every software job, I’ve worked on design systems: high-touch official design systems, migrating various legacy components and style guides to one true design system, and building design systems from scratch.</p>

<p>I especially enjoy design system work because I get to closely collaborate with engineering, design, product, and other stakeholders. I believe that a great design system is both practical and delightful to use. It not only speeds up development, but it allows designers and engineers to focus on higher-level problem solving…since building the basics “just works”.</p>

<p>I’m a Bay Area transplant now living in Salt Lake City. When I’m not making the web a better place, I enjoy strolling my dog, gardening, and skiing.</p>

